# Temporary diagnostic outputs — auto-isolate from tracked scripts.
# Rationale: 2026-05-11 incident — `ls | grep -E '^_phaseA' | xargs rm`
# wiped 4 tracked `_phaseA-*.cjs` files because temp outputs and tracked
# scripts shared the same `_phaseA-` prefix.
#
# Policy:
#   - Tracked scripts/payloads: meaningful names (_phaseA-audit.cjs,
#     _phaseB-prose.cjs, _phaseC-classify.cjs, ...)
#   - One-shot temp outputs: MUST use `_tmp_*` or `_scratch_*` prefix
#     (or `*.tmp.json` / `*.tmp.cjs` suffix). These never collide with
#     tracked names.
#
# See: memory/feedback_worktree_safe_cleanup.md
#      memory/feedback_dirty_folder_rm_pitfall.md

_tmp_*
_scratch_*
*.tmp.json
*.tmp.cjs
